subSubSection.paragraph:
Male postabdomen: Sternite 5 rectangular, broader than wide, no anterior apodeme. Surstylus narrow, subrectangular (
Fig. 41
). Pregonite small, fused with postgonite. Postgonite with lobes narrowly separated, anterior lobe very broad and rounded, posterior lobe sharply pointed. Ejaculatory apodeme relatively large. Basiphallus with moderately sized epiphallus, fairly long, narrow preepiphallus. Distiphallus simple, without apparent dorsal tube (
Fig. 40
).
